DevOps Roadmap (Zero to Hero)
│
├── 1. Basics of OS and Networking
│   ├── Linux
│   │   ├── File Systems
│   │   ├── Basic Shell Commands
│   │   ├── Process Management
│   │   └── Permissions and Users
│   └── Networking Concepts
│       ├── TCP/IP, UDP
│       ├── DNS, DHCP
│       ├── IP Addresses and Subnetting
│       ├── Ports and Protocols
│       └── VPN, Proxy
│
├── 2. Version Control
│   ├── Git (Basic to Advanced)
│   │   ├── Git Branching
│   │   ├── Merging and Rebasing
│   │   ├── Pull Requests and Code Reviews
│   │   └── Git Workflows (e.g., Gitflow, GitHub Flow)
│   └── Git Platforms
│       ├── GitHub
│       ├── GitLab
│       └── Bitbucket
│
├── 3. Scripting and Automation
│   ├── Bash Scripting
│   ├── Python or Go (Choose one)
│   │   ├── Automation Scripts
│   │   ├── File Management
│   │   └── REST API Calls
│   └── PowerShell (for Windows environments)
│
├── 4. Continuous Integration (CI)
│   ├── CI Concepts
│   │   └── Automated Testing, Build Pipelines
│   ├── CI Tools
│   │   ├── Jenkins
│   │   ├── GitLab CI
│   │   └── CircleCI / TravisCI
│   └── Pipelines and Automation
│       ├── Writing Jenkinsfiles (or equivalent)
│       └── Pipeline as Code
│
├── 5. Continuous Delivery and Deployment (CD)
│   ├── CD Concepts
│   │   ├── Blue-Green Deployments
│   │   ├── Canary Releases
│   │   └── Feature Toggles
│   ├── CD Tools
│   │   ├── Jenkins
│   │   ├── Spinnaker
│   │   └── ArgoCD
│   └── Deployment Strategies
│       └── Zero-Downtime Deployments
│
├── 6. Configuration Management
│   ├── Concepts
│   │   ├── Infrastructure as Code (IaC)
│   │   └── Immutable Infrastructure
│   ├── Tools
│   │   ├── Ansible
│   │   ├── Puppet
│   │   └── Chef
│   └── Writing Playbooks/Manifests
│
├── 7. Infrastructure as Code (IaC)
│   ├── Tools
│   │   ├── Terraform
│   │   ├── CloudFormation (AWS)
│   │   └── Pulumi
│   ├── Provisioning Infrastructure
│   ├── Terraform Modules and State Management
│   └── Integrating IaC with CI/CD Pipelines
│
├── 8. Cloud Providers
│   ├── AWS
│   │   ├── EC2, S3, RDS, VPC
│   │   ├── IAM (Identity and Access Management)
│   │   ├── Lambda
│   │   └── CloudWatch / CloudTrail
│   ├── Azure
│   │   ├── Virtual Machines, Storage Accounts
│   │   ├── Azure DevOps
│   │   └── Azure Functions
│   └── GCP (Google Cloud Platform)
│       ├── Compute Engine, Cloud Storage
│       ├── IAM and Roles
│       └── Google Kubernetes Engine (GKE)
│
├── 9. Containers and Orchestration
│   ├── Docker
│   │   ├── Dockerfile
│   │   ├── Docker Compose
│   │   ├── Image Management
│   │   └── Docker Networking and Volumes
│   ├── Kubernetes (K8s)
│   │   ├── Pods, Deployments, Services
│   │   ├── Namespaces and ConfigMaps
│   │   ├── Helm Charts
│   │   └── Ingress and Load Balancing
│   └── Container Registries
│       ├── DockerHub
│       ├── ECR (AWS)
│       └── GCR (GCP)
│
├── 10. Monitoring and Logging
│   ├── Monitoring Tools
│   │   ├── Prometheus
│   │   ├── Grafana
│   │   └── Datadog
│   ├── Logging Tools
│   │   ├── ELK Stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana)
│   │   ├── Fluentd
│   │   └── Graylog
│   └── Alerts and Dashboards
│
├── 11. Security and Compliance
│   ├── Security Best Practices
│   │   ├── Secrets Management
│   │   ├── IAM Policies
│   │   └── Secure Networking (e.g., VPN, VPC)
│   ├── Compliance
│   │   ├── CIS Benchmarks
│   │   └── Cloud Compliance (e.g., PCI-DSS, HIPAA)
│   ├── DevSecOps Integration
│   │   ├── SAST (Static Analysis Security Testing)
│   │   └── DAST (Dynamic Analysis Security Testing)
│   └── Tools
│       ├── HashiCorp Vault
│       ├── Aqua Security
│       └── Falco
│
├── 12. Site Reliability Engineering (SRE) Practices
│   ├── Monitoring and Alerting
│   ├── Error Budgets and SLAs
│   ├── Incident Response
│   ├── Reliability Engineering Metrics
│   └── Automation of Operations Tasks
│
└── 13. Soft Skills and Communication
    ├── Collaboration with Dev and Ops Teams
    ├── Communication Tools (Slack, Teams)
    ├── Understanding Agile and Scrum Methodologies
    └── Leadership and Decision-Making Skills
